DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       These functions place a string of wchar_t characters  from
       the  current or specified window into the array pointed to
       by wstr starting at the current or specified cursor  posi-
       tion and ending at the end of the line.

       These  functions will only store the entire wide character
       sequence associated with a spacing complex  character.  If
       the array is large enough to contain at least one complete
       spacing complex character, the array is filled  with  com-
       plete characters. If the array is not large enough to con-
       tain any complete characters this is an error.

       The and functions store at most n characters in the  array
       pointed to by wstr.

